706215f-a.title: Brooklyn: Park Place - Nostrand Avenue
706215f-a.text:
798-802 Park Place, south side, between Nostrand (left) and Rogers
Aves. (right), showing the gardener cottage of Geo. B. Fish. It formerly
stood in the middle of the block between Park and Sterling Place. In
1925 it was at the present location. It does not appear in the Brooklyn
Atlas of 1929. From 1840 to 1848 it was the home of Geo. B. Fish who was
successively a Railroad Agent, President of the Long Island Railroad and
Merchant.
1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

706218f-a.title: Brooklyn: Park Place - Nostrand Avenue
706218f-a.text:
B1O Park Place, south side, west of Nostrand Ave., showing First
Primitive Methodist Church. Inscription over entrance reads, 'American
Primitive Methodist Society, organized 1841, First Church.
May 27, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
